# WAF rules for brand domain protection.
# Only needed when service has external brand domain endpoints going through Cloudflare.
# File location: IFA/cloudflareplatformproduction (or staging variant)
#
# Placeholders:
#   {{BRAND_DOMAIN}}    — brand domain hostname
#   {{RULE_NAME}}       — descriptive WAF rule name
#   {{ALLOWED_PATHS}}   — comma-separated list of allowed API paths
#
# Note: WAF rules are typically inherited from the existing CloudOps configuration.
# During migration, verify that existing WAF rules still apply correctly when
# traffic is routed to Sonic Runtime. The WAF rules themselves usually don't
# need changes — they operate at the Cloudflare edge before reaching either platform.
#
# If the existing service has WAF rules in cloudflareplatformproduction:
#   1. Identify existing rules: grep -r "{{BRAND_DOMAIN}}" /tmp/cloudflareplatformproduction/
#   2. Verify rules reference the domain, not the origin server
#   3. No changes needed if rules are domain-based (most are)
#   4. If rules reference origin IPs/hostnames, update to include Sonic Runtime origins
